args:
Valerio and Picaro face off in a final round
where contestants must prepare 1,000 plates—
but Valerio must also contend with Picaro's
blatant interference. Trying to turn things
around at the eleventh hour, Valerio and the
gang go on a mad search for ingredients.

The big one is finally here, folks:
The Orichalcum Chef's final round!
Our contestants are two gargantuans of
this galley gauntlet: Picaro and Valerio!
I have been waiting for this moment...\nfor there is no brow better suited for\nthe sweet laurel of victory than Picaro's!
Now let us announce the format for\nthe judging of this final challenge.

In all previous rounds, our esteemed panel
of judges made the decision—but this
time, that lofty task falls to those in the
AUDIENCE as well!
In the final round, our chefs will be asked\nto prepare one thousand servings of their\nbest and most flavorful dish!
The winner will be determined by which\ndining-hall dynamo is the first to\nachieve a thousand empty plates!

Everyone in the Halidom will partake: 
guests and kitchen staff, nobles and 
commoners, from the oldest senior to
the youngest mewling babe!
Which of our bastions of boiling, baking,\nand braising will be the first to delight\neach and every tongue in the house?!
At my signal, chefs, unleash culinary hell.\nOn your marks...get set...COOOOOOOK!
Looks like things have turned\nserious in a hurry, Valerio.

You're flustered because you don't have
any kitchen staff to help out, yeah?
Well, we're here to lend a hand and
get ya outta this trouble casserole!
That would be a huge boon indeed.\nMight I ask you to go and collect\ningredients for me, in that case?

Pipple and I will canvas to the east,
so perhaps you could handle the rest?
I need everything listed on these
recipe cards here.
Consider it done. Let's go, everyone!
Whew. I should be able to manage now.\nI owe the prince and his friends a debt.
Glad to hear it. ...That you'll manage,\nI mean.
Mitsuba? What are you doing here?
Just passing by. ...Okay, fine. I was\nactually wondering how it was going.
Oho ho! Just some associates of mine\nwho have come here to help me slice,\ndice, and fillet you.
Do you have even a modicum\nof pride as a chef?
I would spit in your vichyssoise a thousand\ntimes over if it meant winning the day!\nTHAT is the only pride that matters!

You people with your talk of fairness
and clean competition... Pah! A clear
conscience will not help me achieve
that which I strive to protect!
And what could you possibly be protecting\nthat you'd resort to so many dirty tricks?\nThe reputation of your brand?
What I do, I do for family.\nFor my wife and son.
Ridiculous! You're the head of the world's\nmost famous restaurant—surely your wife\nand son want for nothing!
You are as foolish in this matter as you\nare in the kitchen. Because in truth,\nmy cooking is...disgusting.

My guests are deserting me in droves!
My sweet wife will not even take a nibble!
And if I feed it to my dear boy, he vomits
it up with a horrifying wretch!
Do you know what it feels like to make\nyour beloved child expel his innards?!\n...No. You do not. You COULD not!
You should be relieved that your son\nwas born with a functioning palate.
SILENCE! ...The point is, try as I might,\nI am unable to make food that sends all\nwho eat it into paroxysms of tasty delight.
Yet I have inherited the famed L'Amandier!\nIf she should fail, my family will be tossed\naside into the gutter like potato peelings!
I will do whatever I must to protect my\nrestaurant AND my family! I will lie!\nCheat! Steal! Put pineapple on a pizza!
I care not what it takes so long as I can\nkeep the restaurant alive until my son\nis ready to take the reins.
I can't believe I'm going to say this,\nbut I almost understand you.
And yet, how could you possibly\nlook your son in the eye if this is\nhow you act in his name?
Zip your lips before I ice them shut.\n...Now, my minions! Surround them!
Oho ho ho! It matters not how much of a\nwizard you are in the kitchen if you can't\nhold your own in a proper scrap!
Even a genius chef is but pan drippings\non the battlefield. Now cook his goose...\nand render the skin EXTRA CRISPY!
A genius chef, you say? Ah,\nbut I fear you're mistaken.
By my sainted duck press!\nSuch bladework!
As I said—and how unfortunate for you—\nI am no chef. Instead, I am a knight who\nwas once hailed as a prodigy.

But I am also a damned fool who believed
he could overcome anything so long as he
had strength. And in so doing...I failed to
protect my beloved princess.
If ONLY I was a genius chef!\nIf ONLY that was fate's path for me!
Had I cast aside my sword for a sauce pan,\nI would never have watched her die!
I can't taste anything...\nI want something good...
You want to protect your family, Picaro?
How dare you! At least you HAVE family!
You possess something far more amazing\nthan anything I will ever do!
Enough! Leave Valerio! He will julienne\nus into pieces if we continue!
Go for his ingredients! Wreck them all!
Well, we manged to drive 'em off,\nbut your ingredients are a sorry mess.
I can't make a hundred servings with this,\nnever mind a thousand.
The blame lies with Picaro alone.
No, I mean, I'm sorry for earlier when\nI said your dream wasn't important.

This has something to do with that
blue ribbon, right? I was wondering
why someone like you carried around
such a high-quality item.
It's from your princess. Isn't it?
I ran my mouth and said awful things\nwhen I didn't really know you at all.
It is only natural to look upon the dream\nof a stranger and find it wanting when\nplaced aside one's own.
I seek to serve delicious food to the people\nof the world. I suspect there are many who\nmight consider that a frivolous hobby.

However, some lives can only be saved
with food—happiness is unattainable
without it. Thus must I win the day,
and with all haste.

If I can emerge as the Orichalcum Chef
and open restaurants around the world,
I might be able to erase my tragedies.
...Or so I once believed.
I see. Your dream isn't to become famous.\nIt's to have what comes AFTER fame.
Yes. But sadly, it has slipped away.\nI have no choice but to withdraw.
You can use the ingredients I set aside\nfor if I made it to the finals!
You would do this for me?
You bet! And then we'll have the folks\nfrom the Halidom help track down the\nrest of whatever you need!
PLUS, I'll even help you prep.\nC'mon, you can't give up now!
Honestly? If people think I helped save the\nOrichalcum Chef's bacon, it's gonna be\nincredible publicity for our restaurant.
Then I suppose we should get busy.
You guys, go out there and grab anything\nedible that isn't covered in mold!
Uh, but aren't you gonna end up with,\nlike, four million totally rando things?
Leave it to me. I will take any and all\ningredients and transform them into\nthe most flavorful dishes imaginable!
And with me as your kitchen grunt,\nyou're gonna win this for sure!
I swear I will see your ingredients become\nthe road that leads to my victory!
